cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.MM, cs.AI, cs.CR 

The paper deals with person re-identification, which is a computer vision problem, and proposes a new attention mechanism to improve the performance of existing methods. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also introduces a new network architecture that explicitly enhances the discrimination and richness of attention knowledge, which suggests that it could also belong to cs.LG (Machine Learning). Additionally, the paper uses large-scale datasets to validate the proposed method, which could also place it in the categories cs.MM (Multimedia) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Finally, the paper discusses the potential impact of their work on security applications, which could suggest that it belongs to cs.CR (Cryptography and Security).
